originalText.text: I had a great experience at Queen of Queens Nails. Everyone is so nice. Clean place with lots of color options. I opt out for the cat eye gel nails and I love them! Free coffee or tea. And don’t forget about the shoulder massage after my mani! That’s the best. Definitely coming back. Thank you!

originalText.text: I enjoyed my nail service at this salon. It is very reasonably priced for the service, cleanliness and atmosphere. The techs are all wonderful and efficient. I was happy with my nails and time at the spa. They offer facials, waxing and more aside from nail services. Thank you Cindy for a relaxing afternoon! I look forward to my future visits.

originalText.text: Like every nail salon, it's the technician that matters and I have tried many. Yana and Irene are hit and miss. Susan is excellent every time!  She's a perfectionist, and you NEVER have to worry about how your nails will turn out.  This nail salon is expensive compared to others in the neighborhood.  So much so that I had to reduce my frequency and find another salon to do my  pedicure.  I keep coming back because the salon itself is aesthetically pleasing and Susan is amazing.

originalText.text: This place is awesome. I had the best experience doing my nails and the foot massage was much needed after a week of walking in the city. The store is really well maintained and very roomy. The ambience this place offers is one of the best. Most places I've been to only offer one kind of service. This place offers it all! From nails to massage, to facials and eyebrows, you name it and they'll deliver. I was very indecisive on what I wanted to do, so I just had them recommend and it was the best experience I've had thus far. Give this place a try and you won't regret it!

originalText.text:
Very rude, overpriced!
Almost 200$ for gel mani & pedi.
Had my nails done with rhinestones for OVER 100$! The lady who was doing my nails kept telling me that she’s in a rush and that I’m takin up too much time which made me very uncomfortable. If they don’t want to do the work, don’t accept it in the first place! I was clear on what I wanted from the beginning.
3 of the rhinestones came off the NEXT DAY. I walk in and when I tell the lady what’s wrong she jumps at me saying that guarantee is “only for color and only for 5 days” - which is an absolutely unacceptable answer. I asked “so I pay >100$ for a manicure that lasts less than ONE DAY?” She then insisted 5 days had passed, she wasn’t able to calculate correctly. After fighting for my right they fixed the nails (very poorly).

Just do yourself the favor and don’t come here.
